  "debug_data_path": "debug_data/2020_762",
  "eprint": {
    "title": "Functional Encryption for Attribute-Weighted Sums from $k$-Lin",
    "authors": [
      {
        "name": "Michel Abdalla",
        "email": "abdalla@ens",
        "affiliation": ""
      },
      {
        "name": "Junqing Gong",
        "email": "frjqgong@sei",
        "affiliation": ""
      },
      {
        "name": "Hoeteck Wee",
        "email": "cnwee@di",
        "affiliation": ""
      }
    ],
    "abstract": "We present functional encryption schemes for attribute-weighted sums, where encryption takes as input $N$ attribute-value pairs $(x_i,z_i)$ where $x_i$ is public and $z_i$ is private; secret keys are associated with arithmetic branching programs $f$, and decryption returns the weighted sum $\\sum_{i=1}^N f(x_i) z_i$ while leaking no additional information about the $z_i$'s. Our main construction achieves\n\n(1) compact public parameters and key sizes that are independent of $N$ and the secret key can decrypt a ciphertext for any a-prior unbounded $N$;\n\n(2) short ciphertexts that grow with $N$ and the size of $z_i$ but not $x_i$;\n\n(3) simulation-based security against unbounded collusions;\n\n(4) relies on the standard $k$-linear assumption in prime-order bilinear groups.",
    "keywords": [],
